# Tailwind CSS Guidelines

## Styling Principles
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Use Tailwind's design tokens for consistency
- Implement dark mode support using Tailwind
- Avoid custom CSS unless absolutely necessary
- Use Tailwind's component layer for reusable styles

## Responsive Design
- Start with mobile styles (no prefix)
- Use `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`, `2xl:` for larger screens
- Implement consistent spacing using Tailwind's scale
- Use flexbox and grid utilities for layouts

## Component Patterns
```html
<!-- Card Component -->
<div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
  <!-- Content -->
</div>

<!-- Button Component -->
<button class="bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded-md transition-colors">
  Click me
</button>

<!-- Grid Layout -->
<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
  <!-- Items -->
</div>
```

## Dark Mode
- Use `dark:` prefix for dark mode variants
- Implement consistent color schemes
- Test both light and dark modes
